## Component Conversion

### 1. Basic Component — HTML Tags → Native Components

**React Web:**

```tsx
export default function ProductCard({ name, price }) {
    return (
        <div className="border rounded p-4">
            <h3 className="font-bold text-lg">{name}</h3>
            <p className="text-gray-500">${price}</p>
        </div>
    );
}
```

**React Native:**

```tsx
import { View, Text, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

export default function ProductCard({ name, price }: { name: string; price: number }) {
    return (
        // div → View
        <View style={styles.card}>
            {/* All text MUST be inside <Text> — no bare strings */}
            <Text style={styles.name}>{name}</Text>
            <Text style={styles.price}>${price.toFixed(2)}</Text>
        </View>
    );
}

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
    card: {
        borderWidth: 1,
        borderColor: '#e5e7eb',
        borderRadius: 8,
        padding: 16,
    },
    name: {
        fontWeight: 'bold',
        fontSize: 18,
    },
    price: {
        color: '#6b7280',
        marginTop: 4,
    },
});
```

---

### 2. Button / Click → Pressable / onPress

**React Web:**

```tsx
<button onClick={() => handleDelete(id)} className="bg-red-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">
    Delete
</button>
```

**React Native:**

```tsx
import { Pressable, Text, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

<Pressable
    onPress={() => handleDelete(id)}
    style={({ pressed }) => [styles.button, pressed && styles.buttonPressed]}
>
    <Text style={styles.buttonText}>Delete</Text>
</Pressable>

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
    button: { backgroundColor: '#ef4444', paddingHorizontal: 16, paddingVertical: 8, borderRadius: 8 },
    buttonPressed: { opacity: 0.7 },
    buttonText: { color: '#fff' },
});
```

> Use `Pressable` (preferred) or `TouchableOpacity`. Never use `div` with `onClick` for interactive elements in React Native.

---

### 3. Text Input

**React Web:**

```tsx
<input
    type="text"
    value={name}
    onChange={e => setName(e.target.value)}
    placeholder="Enter name"
    className="border rounded px-3 py-2"
/>
```

**React Native:**

```tsx
import { TextInput, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

<TextInput
    value={name}
    onChangeText={setName}            // No event object — just the string value
    placeholder="Enter name"
    style={styles.input}
    autoCapitalize="none"
    keyboardType="default"
/>

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
    input: {
        borderWidth: 1,
        borderColor: '#d1d5db',
        borderRadius: 8,
        paddingHorizontal: 12,
        paddingVertical: 8,
        fontSize: 16,
    },
});
```

> `onChangeText` receives the value string directly — no `e.target.value` needed.

---

### 4. Scrollable Lists

**React Web:**

```tsx
<div className="overflow-y-auto h-64">
    {products.map(p => <ProductCard key={p.id} product={p} />)}
</div>
```

**React Native — ScrollView (small lists):**

```tsx
import { ScrollView } from 'react-native';

<ScrollView>
    {products.map(p => <ProductCard key={p.id} product={p} />)}
</ScrollView>
```

**React Native — FlatList (large/infinite lists, preferred):**

```tsx
import { FlatList } from 'react-native';

<FlatList
    data={products}
    keyExtractor={item => item.id.toString()}
    renderItem={({ item }) => <ProductCard product={item} />}
    ItemSeparatorComponent={() => <View style={{ height: 12 }} />}
    onEndReached={loadMore}        // pagination
    onEndReachedThreshold={0.5}
/>
```

> Prefer `FlatList` over `ScrollView + map` for any list that might grow — it only renders visible items.

---

### 5. Images

**React Web:**

```tsx
<img src={product.imageUrl} alt={product.name} className="w-full h-48 object-cover" />
```

**React Native:**

```tsx
import { Image, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

<Image
    source={{ uri: product.imageUrl }}
    style={styles.image}
    resizeMode="cover"
/>

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
    image: { width: '100%', height: 192 },
});
```

